# gstack workflow routing

Use these project skills when relevant:
- `gstack-office-hours`: when framing is fuzzy or the user asks to rethink the product
- `gstack-plan-ceo-review`: when a plan exists but scope/differentiation needs pushback
- `gstack-plan-eng-review`: when implementing and architecture/test plan must be locked
- `gstack-plan-design-review`: when UI/IA needs restraint and anti-slop checks
- `gstack-design-html`: when producing HTML mockups
- `gstack-review`: before shipping non-trivial code changes
- `gstack-qa-only`: when asked to test flows and report bugs (no code changes)
- `gstack-ship`: when asked to finalize/ship

Guardrails:
- No generic learning-app patterns.
- Prefer restraint over richness.
- Keep outputs short, high-signal, non-repetitive.

